#Text=BDSM as business : Interviews with Dominatrixes
#Text=Sunday , October 28 , 2007
#Text=Whether the Civil War , World War II or the Iraq War , it can be challenging to face how conflict
#Text=penetrates the psyche of a nation and surfaces in the nuances of life .
#Text=There are thousands — if not millions — of individuals who indulge in fantasies others would deem perverse that have their nascence in some of the darkest moments of human history .
#Text=It is possible someone you know pays a person to dress like a German Nazi to treat them like a “ dirty Jew ” , or to force them to pick cotton off the floor like a slave .
#Text=An S&M dungeon is a place where these individuals act out such taboos .
#Text=Businesses that operate to meet their needs are often hidden , but they do exist and are typically legal .
#Text=The clients want to remain confidential for fear of ostracism in their respective communities .
#Text=As Sigmund Freud wrote , " Anyone who has violated a taboo becomes taboo himself because he possesses the dangerous quality of tempting others to follow his example .

column1: #Text=The interview was neither sensational nor typical , but what you read may surprise , repulse , or even awaken feelings you never knew you had .
#Text=Below is David Shankbone 's interview with three Dominatrixes .
#Text=Starting out
#Text=David Shankbone : How did you get started as an S&M Mistress ?
#Text=Alex : I ’m from California and I started out by playing in various fetish clubs and I had different play partners .
#Text=I just kind of dabbled in my personal life .

#Text=When I moved to New York a few years ago , I was doing the same thing with friends and I realized I was getting bored hanging out with the same people all the time — they became good friends , but I met another pro-dom .
#Text=I was talking to her about it and realized I could end up experiencing so many different things in a place like this .
#Text=And it ’s true .
#Text=I meet so many different people who are into all these different things .
#Text=I ’m all about variety .
